Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the blocked tile damage/life system. Let me compile the findings into a detailed report.

## BLOCKED TILE DAMAGE/LIFE SYSTEM - COMPREHENSIVE ANALYSIS

### 1. HOW BLOCKED TILES WITH LIVES ARE CREATED

**Tile Creation Function** (`tile-helpers.js` lines 54-63):
```javascript
export function createBlockedWithLifeTile(lifeValue, immovable = true) {
    return {
        type: TILE_TYPE.BLOCKED_WITH_LIFE,
        value: null,
        lifeValue: lifeValue,
        immovable: immovable,
        specialType: null,
        hasBeenSwapped: false,
    };
}
```

**Board Placement** (`board.js` lines 95-98):
- Created during board initialization via `createBoard()` function
- Configured through level config with `blockedTiles` array: `{ row: 2, lifeValue: 128 }` or `{ row: 3, col: 4, lifeValue: 64 }`
- Also supports rectangular blocks: `{ row: 2, col: 3, width: 2, height: 2, lifeValue: 124 }`
- Also rectangular blocks stored via `createRectangularBlockedTile()` (line 105-126)

**Properties:**
- `type`: BLOCKED_WITH_LIFE (from TILE_TYPE)
- `lifeValue`: The current health/hit points (number like 8, 16, 32, 64, 128, 256, 512, 1024)
- `immovable`: Whether blocked by gravity (true by default)
- `rectId`, `rectAnchor`, `rectWidth`, `rectHeight`: Only for rectangular blocks

---

### 2. HOW DAMAGE IS APPLIED (LIFECYCLE)

**Damage Application** (`merge-processor.js` lines 465-697, specifically 505-543 & 638-652):

**Step 1: Detecting Adjacent Blocked Tiles (lines 488-495)**
```javascript
adjacentPositions.forEach((pos) => {
    if (isBlockedWithLife(tile)) {
        const key = isRectangularBlocked(tile) ? tile.rectId : `${pos.row}_${pos.col}`;
        if (hitInThisGroup.has(key)) return; // Don't hit twice per match
        hitInThisGroup.add(key);

        // Calculate damage value from the MATCHED tiles (not merged result)
        const damageValue = getDisplayValue(group.value);
```

**Step 2: Accumulating Damage (lines 515-542)**
- Track all adjacent blocked tiles to damage
- Store in `goalTilesToDamage` array with:
  - `key`: unique identifier
  - `row`, `col`: position
  - `damage`: display value of matched tiles
  - `targetPos`: closest merge position for animation reference
  - `tile`: reference to the blocked tile

**Step 3: Applying Damage (lines 638-652)**
```javascript
goalTilesToDamage.forEach((entry) => {
    const tile = game.board[entry.row][entry.col];
    if (isBlockedWithLife(tile)) {
        tile.lifeValue -= entry.damage;  // APPLY DAMAGE
        // If life goes below or equal to 0, mark for removal
        if (tile.lifeValue <= 0) {
            blockedTilesToRemove.push({
                row: entry.row,
                col: entry.col,
                targetPos: entry.targetPos,
            });
        }
    }
});
```

**Damage Calculation:**
- Damage = display value of matched tiles (NOT merged value)
- Example: 3 tiles of value 4 (internal) = 3 × 16 = 48 damage to adjacent blocked tile
- Multiple adjacent matches on same blocked tile = accumulate damage

**When Applied:**
- After match detection, BEFORE animations start
- Called via `unblockAdjacentTiles()` in `processMatches()` (merge-processor.js line 94)

---

### 3. HOW BLOCKED TILES ARE RENDERED

**Rendering DOM Elements** (`renderer.js` lines 98-222):

**For Regular Single-Cell Blocked Tiles with Life** (lines 149-151):
```javascript
} else if (isBlockedWithLife(tile)) {
    gem.className = `gem tile-BLOCKED_WITH_LIFE`;
    gem.dataset.life = tile.lifeValue;
}
```

**For Rectangular Blocked Tiles with Life** (lines 62-65):
```javascript
if (tile.type === TILE_TYPE.BLOCKED_WITH_LIFE) {
    gem.className = `gem tile-BLOCKED_WITH_LIFE rectangular-blocked`;
    gem.dataset.life = tile.lifeValue;
}
```

**CSS Classes Applied:**
- `.gem`: base tile class
- `.tile-BLOCKED_WITH_LIFE`: style for life-based blocked tiles
- `.rectangular-blocked`: for multi-cell blocks
- `data-life`: HTML5 data attribute storing current lifeValue

**DOM Attributes:**
- `data-row`, `data-col`: position for single cells
- `data-rect-id`, `data-rect-width`, `data-rect-height`: for rectangular blocks
- `data-life`: current lifeValue (may be updated dynamically via CSS custom properties)

**CSS Styling** (`style.css` lines 76-79):
```css
--tile-blocked-bg: #3c3c3c;           /* Dark gray background */
--tile-blocked-border: #666;           /* Medium gray border */
--tile-blocked-x-color: #666;          /* X mark color */
--tile-blocked-life-color: #fff;       /* Life value text color (white) */
```

---

### 4. HOW `showPowerUpRewardAnimation` WORKS (Reference for Floating Text)

**Function** (`game.js` lines 907-970):

**Floating Text Animation Elements:**
```javascript
showPowerUpRewardAnimation(powerUpType) {
    // 1. Create container
    const container = document.createElement("div");
    container.className = "formation-powerup-animation";

    // 2. Create headline with stroked text custom element
    const headline = document.createElement("stroked-text");
    headline.className = "formation-powerup-headline";
    headline.setAttribute("text", "Great!");  // Random motivational word
    headline.setAttribute("font-size", "48");
    headline.setAttribute("stroke-width", "12");
    headline.setAttribute("fill", "#FFD700");  // Gold
    headline.setAttribute("stroke", "#333");   // Dark outline

    // 3. Create subtitle with "+1" and icon
    const subtitleContainer = document.createElement("div");
    subtitleContainer.className = "formation-powerup-subtitle";
    // Contains "+1 🔨" (icon varies by type: 🔨 hammer, ✂️ halve, 🔄 swap)

    // 4. Append to body and let CSS animation run
    document.body.appendChild(container);

    // Auto-remove after animation completes
    setTimeout(() => container.remove(), 1500);
}
```

**Animation Approach:**
- Uses CSS animation class `.formation-powerup-animation`
- Floating upward with fade-out effect
- Duration ~1500ms
- Positioned at center of screen
- Custom `<stroked-text>` element for bold outlined text

---

### 5. EXISTING SHAKE/DAMAGE ANIMATIONS IN CSS

**Current Animation Keyframes** (`style.css` lines 163-192):

```css
@keyframes unblock-move {
    0% {
        transform: scale(1);
        opacity: 1;
    }
    50% {
        transform: scale(0.8);
        opacity: 0.7;
    }
    100% {
        transform: scale(0.3);
        opacity: 0;
    }
}

@keyframes popShrink {
    0% {
        transform: scale(1);
    }
    20% {
        transform: scale(1.1);  /* Briefly expand */
    }
    100% {
        transform: scale(0);
    }
}

.disappear {
    animation: popShrink 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94) forwards;
}
```

**Note:** No built-in shake animation exists. The system uses:
- Scale transformations (expand then shrink)
- Opacity fading
- Cubic-bezier easing for bounce effect

---

### 6. HOW `animateUnblocking` WORKS

**Function** (`animator.js` lines 260-321):

**Three Types of Blocked Tile Removal:**

**Type 1: Individual Cell Removal (Merge-Count Blocks)**
```javascript
if (blockedEntry.isMergeCount && !blockedEntry.isFullRemoval) {
    const blockedElement = document.querySelector(`[data-rect-id="${tile.rectId}"]`);
    if (blockedElement) {
        const xMarker = blockedElement.querySelector(`[data-cell-key="${cellKey}"]`);
        if (xMarker) {
            xMarker.classList.add("cell-x-removing");
            setTimeout(() => xMarker.remove(), 300 * speedMultiplier);
        }
    }
}
```

**Type 2: Full Rectangular Block Removal**
```javascript
if (blockedEntry.isFullRemoval && isRectangularBlocked(tile)) {
    animateRectangularBlockRemoval(game, tile, speedMultiplier);
    // Adds "disappear" class, removes from all cells after 400ms
}
```

**Type 3: Single-Cell Blocked Tile**
```javascript
const blockedElement = document.querySelector(`[data-row="${row}"][data-col="${col}"]`);
if (blockedElement) {
    blockedElement.classList.add("disappear");  // Triggers popShrink animation
}
setTimeout(() => {
    game.board[blockedEntry.row][blockedEntry.col] = null;
}, 400 * speedMultiplier);
```

**Animation Timing:**
- Adds CSS class (`disappear` or `cell-x-removing`)
- CSS animation plays for 300-400ms
- After animation, remove from DOM and board data
- `speedMultiplier` parameter slows animations after tutorials (2x slower)

**Callbacks:**
```javascript
setTimeout(() => {
    updateBlockedTileGoalsCallback();  // Update goal progress
    updateGoalDisplayCallback(false);  // Refresh UI without checking completion
}, 400 * speedMultiplier);
```

---

### 7. `unblockAdjacentTiles` FULL LIFECYCLE

**Called From:** `processMatches()` line 94 in merge-processor.js

**Complete Flow:**

```
1. For each match group:
   - Get target positions (where merged tiles will be)
   - Calculate damage value from matched tiles

2. For each matched tile in group:
   - Check all 4 adjacent positions (up, down, left, right)

3. For each adjacent tile:
   IF blocked-with-life:
      - Calculate unique key (rectId or row_col)
      - Skip if already hit by this match group
      - Mark tile for damage: record (row, col, damage, targetPos)

   ELSE IF merge-count block:
      - Track per-cell merge counts
      - Mark specific cell for removal

   ELSE IF regular blocked:
      - Mark for complete removal

4. Apply damage:
   - Subtract damage from lifeValue
   - If lifeValue <= 0: mark for removal

5. Animate removal:
   - Call animateUnblocking() with blockedTilesToRemove array
   - Adds CSS animation class
   - Removes from board after 400ms

6. Update goals:
   - updateBlockedTileGoals(): increment "blocked" goal count
   - updateGoalDisplay(false): refresh UI
```

**Key Properties:**
- `hitInThisGroup`: Set to prevent same block being hit twice by same match
- `damageValue`: `getDisplayValue(group.value)` - display value of matched tiles
- `closestTarget`: used for animation direction hint

---

### SUMMARY TABLE

| Aspect | Details |
|--------|---------|
| **Creation** | `createBlockedWithLifeTile(lifeValue)` in tile-helpers.js |
| **Properties** | `type`, `lifeValue`, `immovable`, `rectId` (for rectangular) |
| **Damage Source** | Display value of matched adjacent tiles |
| **Damage Application** | Subtracted from `lifeValue` in unblockAdjacentTiles() |
| **Removal Trigger** | When `lifeValue <= 0` |
| **Animation** | `disappear` class → `popShrink` keyframe (0.4s) |
| **CSS Classes** | `.tile-BLOCKED_WITH_LIFE`, `.rectangular-blocked` |
| **Data Attributes** | `data-life`, `data-row`, `data-col`, `data-rect-id` |
| **Rendering** | Single DOM element per tile/rectangle |
| **Animation Pattern** | Scale from 1→1.1→0, opacity 1→0 |
| **Timing** | Damage applied before animations; removal after 400ms |
| **Goal Updates** | `updateBlockedTileGoals()` increments progress |

